        'Sepsis can occur without fever - hypothermia actually indicates worse prognosis',
        'Lactate >4 indicates severe tissue hypoperfusion even with normal blood pressure',
        'Source control is as important as antibiotics - look for drainable collections',
        'Mental status changes may be the first sign of sepsis, especially in elderly',
