        level2: 'Iron is needed to make hemoglobin, the protein in red blood cells that carries oxygen. Without enough iron, your body makes smaller, paler red cells that are less effective. Finding why you are low on iron is important.',
        level3: 'IDA presents with microcytic, hypochromic anemia. Diagnose with low ferritin (<30), low iron, high TIBC. Always identify the cause - in men and postmenopausal women, GI workup is essential to rule out occult malignancy.',
